cdx6500PPCTATMPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTATMPortTable
cdx6500PPCTATMPortTable.description: This table contains ATM Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500PPCTATMPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTATMPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTATMPortEntry.description: Entries in the ATM Port Configuration Table.

atmPCfgMaxVPIRange.name: atmPCfgMaxVPIRange
atmPCfgMaxVPIRange.description: This parameter specifies the maximum VPI value that any station on this port can operate with. Increasing this value has the effect of decreasing the maximum VPI that can be specified .

atmPCfgMaxVCIRange.name: atmPCfgMaxVCIRange
atmPCfgMaxVCIRange.description: This parameter specifies the maximum VCI value that any station on this port can operate with. Increasing this value has the effect of decreasing the maximum VCI that can be specified .

atmPCfgLinkAssuranceTimer.name: atmPCfgLinkAssuranceTimer
atmPCfgLinkAssuranceTimer.description: If PVC Link Assurance Method is set to LOOPBACK, this is the amount of time in seconds between sending F5 loopback cells .

atmPCfgLinkAssuranceCount.name: atmPCfgLinkAssuranceCount
atmPCfgLinkAssuranceCount.description: If PVC Link Assurance Method is set to LOOPBACK, this is the number of retries sent before declaring that the link is down .

atmPCfgCCActDeactTimer.name: atmPCfgCCActDeactTimer
atmPCfgCCActDeactTimer.description: If PVC Link Assurance Method is set to NEGOTIATE CC cells this is the amount of time in seconds between retransmissions of Activate or Deactivate cells.

atmPCfgCCActDeactCount.name: atmPCfgCCActDeactCount
atmPCfgCCActDeactCount.description: If PVC Link Assurance Method is set to NEGOTIATE CC cells this is the number of times to send an Activate or Deactivate cell before declaring that the negotiation procedure has failed .

atmPCfgVCCTrafficPrioritization.name: atmPCfgVCCTrafficPrioritization
atmPCfgVCCTrafficPrioritization.description: All station VCCs that operate on the port must run with the same traffic prioritization dicipline. This port parameter specifies the priorization as follows: DISABLE - There is no prioritization of traffic within a VCC. SEQUENCE - High priority and normal priority traffic are placed in separate queues which are serviced in sequential round robin order. PRIORITY - High priority and normal priority traffic are placed in separate queues. The high priority queue is serviced completely before the low priority queue.

cdx6500SPCTATMStationTable.description: This table contains ATM Station configuration parameters.

cdx6500SPCTATMStationEntry.name: cdx6500SPCTATMStationEntry
cdx6500SPCTATMStationEntry.description: Entries in the ATM Station Configuration Table.

atmSCfgPortNumber.name: atmSCfgPortNumber
atmSCfgPortNumber.description: The ATM port number corresponding to this station.

atmSCfgStnNumber.name: atmSCfgStnNumber
atmSCfgStnNumber.description: The number of the configured ATM Station.

atmSCfgVPI.name: atmSCfgVPI
atmSCfgVPI.description: The Virtual Path Identifier (VPI) is the provisioned virtual path number for the station of circuit type PVC on the ATM port.

atmSCfgVCI.name: atmSCfgVCI
atmSCfgVCI.description: The Virtual Circuit Identifier (VCI) is the provisioned virtual circuit number for the station of circuit type PVC on the ATM port.

atmSCfgLinkAssuranceMethod.name: atmSCfgLinkAssuranceMethod
atmSCfgLinkAssuranceMethod.description: PVC link assurance method to use: DISABLED - No checking is performed LOOPBACK - Periodically send a loopback cell NEGOTIATE - Negotiate use of CC cells ENABLED - Always use CC cells .

atmSCfgTrafficServiceCategory.name: atmSCfgTrafficServiceCategory
atmSCfgTrafficServiceCategory.description: The service category is the traffic type for the operation of the station. The traffic types are: UBR - Unspecified Bit Rate CBR - Constant Bit Rate VBR - Variable Bit Rate.

atmSCfgPeakCellRate.name: atmSCfgPeakCellRate
atmSCfgPeakCellRate.description: This parameter (PCR) specifies the rate (cells per second) the network agrees to receive cells from the station PCR is configuredin multiples of 20 cells per second.

atmSCfgVBRTrafficShaping.name: atmSCfgVBRTrafficShaping
atmSCfgVBRTrafficShaping.description: Specifies whether a station configured for VBR traffic category conforms to single or dual leaky bucket traffic shaping. Single leaky bucket means the traffic is shaped to only a PCR. Dual bucket shaping means traffic is shaped to PCR as well as SCR and MBS. SINGLE - Single Bucket VBR DUAL - Dual Bucket VBR.

atmSCfgVCCPriorityLevel.name: atmSCfgVCCPriorityLevel
atmSCfgVCCPriorityLevel.description: This parameter controls the priority of the station VCC in comparison to other stations within the same service category (either UBR or VBR). For VBR traffic category, setting this parameter to HIGH classifies a VCC as VBRrt (VBR real time). For VBRnrt (non-real time) select NORMAL. NORMAL - Normal priority HIGH - High priority.

atmSCfgSustainableCellRate.name: atmSCfgSustainableCellRate
atmSCfgSustainableCellRate.description: This parameter (SCR) specifies the rate (cells per second) the network agrees to receive cells from the station. This parameter characterizes the amount of sustainable bandwidth for VBR traffic class. The SCR cannot be greater than the link speed: 3620 for T1, 4800 for E1, 105500 for T3 (96000 for PLCP), 81040 for E3.

atmSCfgMaximumBustSize.name: atmSCfgMaximumBustSize
atmSCfgMaximumBustSize.description: Maximum burst size for VBR traffic in cells
